## Phase 3: Transaction Cost Sensitivity

Sweep cost assumptions and report the breakeven and critical thresholds.

Cost levels to test: 0bps, 2bps, 5bps, 10bps, 20bps, 50bps (all-in round-trip)

```
Transaction Cost Sensitivity:
┌──────────┬────────┬────────┐
│ Cost     │ Sharpe │ Return │
├──────────┼────────┼────────┤
│ 0 bps    │  X.XX  │  XX.X% │
│ 2 bps    │  X.XX  │  XX.X% │
│ 5 bps    │  X.XX  │  XX.X% │
│ 10 bps   │  X.XX  │  XX.X% │
│ 20 bps   │  X.XX  │  XX.X% │
│ 50 bps   │  X.XX  │  XX.X% │
└──────────┴────────┴────────┘

Breakeven cost (Sharpe = 0.0): XX bps
Sharpe 0.5 threshold cost:     XX bps
```

Flag if the Sharpe 0.5 threshold is below 10bps for large-cap strategies or below 30bps for small-cap strategies. These thresholds are achievable by most institutional trading desks.

